cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to extract lexical simplifications from Wikipedia. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques to extract relevant metadata from Wikipedia edit histories. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning models (cs.LG) and deep learning techniques (cs.DL) to derive simplification probabilities. Finally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques to automatically extract lexical simplifications.
